Police say two people in the truck sustained no injuries, and the families of the deceased are yet to be notified. JOHANNESBURG - Four people have been killed when the Polo Vivo they were travelling in collided head-on with a fuel transporting truck in Tomburke in Limpopo.The incident took place on Sunday morning on the R572 where all the deceased were certified dead on the scene.Police say two people in the truck sustained no injuries, and the families of the deceased are yet to be notified.Spokesperson Mamphaswa Seabi said, Police in Tomburke are busy investigating a case of culpable homicide after an accident happened around 6am today. 